@BenCheshire: The "combat damage to you" means that you the player lost life as a result of combat. The creatures are only destroyed and tokens created if you take a hit yourself either by not blocking, by trample damage to you or from "Super Trample" (Deals damage as though it was not blocked).   

A quick word for people on what "Protection from creatures" entitles you, since it seems many players don't fully understand protection. Any damage that would be dealt to Teysa by a creature, either from combat or from abilities of that creature is prevented. (as are any effects that would be reliant on that damage being dealt) Additionally any abilities creatures have that use the word "target" cannot choose her as a target, this includes the abilities of your own creatures. (e.g. [Gigantomancer](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Gigantomancer)) She cannot be blocked by creatures, making her unblockable. The other effect of protection (Preventing enchantment/equipping by protected sources) is generally irrelevent.  

